WEBVTT

00:00:00.031 --> 00:00:02.118
A radiation machine gave one patient

00:00:02.118 --> 00:00:04.277
roughly a hundred times the intended dose.

00:00:05.259 --> 00:00:07.343
The manufacturer said it was impossible.

00:00:08.224 --> 00:00:09.105
Then it happened again.

00:00:09.147 --> 00:00:11.541
The Therac twenty-five replaced physical

00:00:11.541 --> 00:00:14.555
safety interlocks with software checks.

00:00:15.436 --> 00:00:18.277
During fast data entry, a race condition

00:00:18.277 --> 00:00:20.860
could leave the machine in the wrong

00:00:20.860 --> 00:00:23.443
state and fire a full-power beam with

00:00:23.443 --> 00:00:25.781
no filter. Nobody caught it because the

00:00:25.781 --> 00:00:28.147
code had been reused from older machines,

00:00:28.147 --> 00:00:30.304
and reused code felt like tested code.

00:00:31.246 --> 00:00:33.852
Operators reported errors. The

00:00:33.852 --> 00:00:36.515
manufacturer insisted the machine was

00:00:36.515 --> 00:00:38.779
safe. More patients were burned before the

00:00:38.779 --> 00:00:40.146
pattern was treated as real.

00:00:40.185 --> 00:00:43.215
The disaster was not just bad code.

00:00:43.896 --> 00:00:46.025
It was a system with no independent

00:00:46.025 --> 00:00:48.228
safety layer, no quick way to believe

00:00:48.228 --> 00:00:50.725
field reports, and no design for software

00:00:50.725 --> 00:00:54.295
being wrong. That is how small causes

00:00:54.295 --> 00:00:56.412
become massive consequences.
